The paper deals with the problem of learning from examples and function reconstruction, which are core topics in machine learning. It also focuses on regularization in reproducing kernel Hilbert spaces (RKHSs), which is a widely used technique in machine learning. However, the paper specifically addresses the issue of system identification, which is a subfield of control theory and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SI (Signal Processing).
